<br /><br />COLLECTION OF PERSONAL INFORMATION 
This website collects personal information directly from you when you register to use the services offered by The Site. This personal information includes your name, email address, phone number and shipping address. We will only collect personal information from you to the extent deemed reasonably necessary to best offer our services to you as set out in the User Agreement. We will endeavor to ensure the security, integrity and privacy of your personal information.<br /><br />A portion of you credit card number is stored(last 4 numbers) the rest is processed and then securely deleted , we use a Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption which encrypts your information before it is sent to us to protect it from unauthorized use. 
We may collect non-personal data concerning the use of The Site. This may include, but is not limited to, pages visited, times and volume of use of the services as well as Traffic Data. Traffic data includes logs, details of networks, time of log-on or access, length of sessions and similar systems data.
<br /><br />HOW this site MAY USE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
Your personal information can be used  for the processing of payments and to personalize your experience of The Site.  We may disclose your personal information to any relevant regulatory body, if legally obliged to do so.
We may choose to collate statistical information about site traffic, sales and other commercial information that we may pass on to trusted third parties, but these statistics will not include any information that can identify you personally. Your personal information may be used for our internal marketing and demographic studies, together with non-personal data to monitor customer patterns so we can consistently improve The Site for our users. <br /><br />COOKIES
A cookie is a piece of information that is stored on your computer's hard drive by your web browser which tracks your movements within websites. Our site uses cookies to keep track of how often you visit our site, etc.

<br /><br />PASSWORD
You are responsible for all actions taken using your User ID and password. We recommends that you do not disclose your password to third parties. If you choose to share your User ID and password or Personal Information with third parties, you are responsible for all actions taken with your User ID and password. If you suspect that your password or account has been compromised, you should immediately change your password.
